* FLOW-MATIC style heapsort description
* (FLOW-MATIC used English-like pseudoinstructions)

(0) READ-ITEM ARR FROM TAPE-1 GIVING ARR-FILE.
(1) COMPARE ARR-COUNT TO SIX ; IF GREATER GO TO OPERATION 10.
(2) STORE TWELVE IN ARR-0.
(3) STORE ELEVEN IN ARR-1.
(4) STORE THIRTEEN IN ARR-2.
(5) STORE FIVE IN ARR-3.
(6) STORE SIX IN ARR-4.
(7) STORE SEVEN IN ARR-5.
(8) TRANSFER N TO SIX.
(9) EXECUTE HEAPIFY-LOOP.
(10) WRITE-ITEM ARR TO OUTPUT.
(11) STOP.

SUBROUTINE HEAPIFY USING PN, PI.
(H1) TRANSFER PI TO LARGEST.
(H2) COMPUTE LEFT = TWO TIMES PI PLUS ONE.
(H3) COMPUTE RIGHT = TWO TIMES PI PLUS TWO.
(H4) IF LEFT LESS-THAN PN AND ARR(LEFT) GREATER-THAN ARR(LARGEST)
     THEN TRANSFER LEFT TO LARGEST.
(H5) IF RIGHT LESS-THAN PN AND ARR(RIGHT) GREATER-THAN ARR(LARGEST)
     THEN TRANSFER RIGHT TO LARGEST.
(H6) IF LARGEST EQUALS PI GO TO RETURN.
(H7) EXCHANGE ARR(PI) WITH ARR(LARGEST).
(H8) EXECUTE HEAPIFY USING PN, LARGEST.
RETURN.
